distraction: I was not doing anything else. I did take a sip of tea in between tasks. My cat meowed at me a couple of times but I ignored her.
strategies: I found it hard to have a strategy because the images flashed on the screen so fast. I tended to concentrate more on the blue or green crosses than on the objects even though I tried to concentrate on the objects more. With some objects I did not know what they were so it was hard to relate them to anything.
easier: I tried to look at old tech and group it together; such as the video camera and the radio. It was easier if I recognized what the object was; because some objects I could not identify. I tried to group by colors - either muted or bright colors. Mostly it was a huge challenge to group the objects together in my mind so fast - I'm old! At 72 I am not as quick as I once was and it seemed overwhelming to remember the objects and what one was with what.
similar: I have not participated in a study that I really consider similar. I have done studies that asked me to complete various cognitive tasks; but cannot remember one where I was specifically trying to remember pairs of two objects; with a flashing color cross in between each pair.
comments: I found the last task; where I dragged objects into the gray area; to be quite challenging. I did manage to group each object with at least one other object; but was not sure that I did it right.
